---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TechArticle',
  headline: 'Sodmaster Technology Stack',
  description: 'Comprehensive overview of the autonomous technology stack powering Sodmaster.',
  url: 'https://sodmaster.online/technology',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Sodmaster Autonomous Corporation',
  },
};
---
<Layout
  title="Technology | Sodmaster Autonomous Stack"
  description="Dive into Sodmaster’s CrewAI architecture, multi-agent orchestration, and integrated API platform."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <section id="stack">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="section-title">Tech Stack Overview</h1>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Sodmaster merges proven enterprise frameworks with autonomous orchestration to deliver reliability, speed, and visibility across
        every business function.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-2 tech-grid">
        <div class="glass-card">
          <h2>Application Layer</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Python 3.11 + FastAPI for high-performance APIs</li>
            <li>PostgreSQL + Redis for stateful agent memory and caching</li>
            <li>TON, Ethereum, and Bitcoin integrations for treasury automation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="glass-card">
          <h2>Autonomy Layer</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>CrewAI orchestrating 50+ agents across Dev, Ops, Finance, and Growth</li>
            <li>OpenAI GPT-4.1 and function-calling pipelines for reasoning and execution</li>
            <li>Observability mesh with Prometheus, Grafana, and GA4 telemetry</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="crewai">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">CrewAI Architecture</h2>
      <div class="glass-card architecture">
        <p>
          Sodmaster’s CrewAI topology organizes agents into specialized squads with defined protocols, shared context windows, and
          zero-copy data exchange. Each squad operates on mission-critical workflows managed by the Strategic Command unit.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Federated governance: executive AI layer coordinates departmental directives</li>
          <li>Shared context fabric: vectorized knowledge base accessible across agents</li>
          <li>Resilient scheduling: workload balancers align compute budgets with SLAs</li>
          <li>Compliance guardrails: policy agents review every action before execution</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Multi-Agent System</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="glass-card">
          <h3>Planning Layer</h3>
          <p>Strategic Commander sets OKRs, orchestrates initiatives, and aligns resources across crews.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass-card">
          <h3>Execution Layer</h3>
          <p>Task-specific agents execute deployments, content, finance, and support workflows with observability feedback.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass-card">
          <h3>Assurance Layer</h3>
          <p>Security and compliance agents validate outputs, perform audits, and coordinate fail-safes in real time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">API Documentation</h2>
      <div class="glass-card api-card">
        <p>
          Access REST and streaming endpoints for embedding Sodmaster capabilities into your enterprise stack. Authentication leverages
          signed JWT credentials with per-agent scopes.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="gradient-button" href="https://docs.sodmaster.online/api">View API Docs</a>
          <a class="ghost-button" href="mailto:hello@sodmaster.online">Request Integration Support</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .tech-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 10px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .architecture {
    display: grid;
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .api-card {
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
  }
</style>
